news.title: Now, 5% green cover must for new town planning schemes in Ahmedabad
news.para: Ahmedabad is poised for a green transformation as the AMC unveils policies mandating green spaces in new town planning schemes, including urban forests using the Miyawaki method. The initiative, set to launch on July 19, also focuses on good construction practices, increased penalties for illegal tree cutting, and the development of diverse green infrastructure across the city.

news.title: Highrise buildings in Prayagraj to undergo mandatory structural safety audits
news.para: Prayagraj introduces mandatory structural safety audits for high-rise buildings exceeding 15 meters, prompted by safety concerns and past fire incidents. Buildings must undergo audits 10 years post-construction, then every five years. Owners or RWAs must address identified risks promptly, or authorities will conduct repairs at their expense, ensuring stricter enforcement and improved safety standards.

news.title: Nagpur civic body penalises 4,890 for occupying public spaces with building material
news.para: Nagpur Municipal Corporation cracked down on illegal encroachments. Over the past six months, NMC acted against 4,658 individuals and 232 builders. They were penalized for placing construction materials on public spaces. The civic body collected Rs 1.16 crore in penalties. The campaign aimed to keep Nagpur clean and pedestrian-friendly. The drive will continue to prevent public disruption.

news.title: Godrej Properties' COO and CEO-Mumbai region resigns
news.para: Godrej Properties sees leadership changes. Vikas Singhal, COO, and Priyansh Kapoor, Zonal CEO-MMR, resign. Amitesh Shah will succeed Kapoor. Sandeep Navlakhe will replace Singhal.

news.title: Lloyds’ promoter family buys apartments in south Mumbai’s Altamount Road for ₹227 crore
news.para: Ravi Agarwal and his family, part of the Lloyds Group promoters, have acquired six sea-view luxury apartments in Mumbai's Kalpataru Prive for over Rs 227 crore. The deal, valued at Rs 1.27 lakh per sq ft, includes a seven-bedroom duplex and 24 car parking slots. This transaction reaffirms Altamount Road's status as a prime residential location.

news.title: Ashwin Sheth Group acquires 4.05-acre land in Goregaon West, Mumbai
news.para: Ashwin Sheth Group has secured development rights for a 4.05-acre land parcel in Goregaon West, Mumbai, from MHADA. The company plans to construct a residential project with an estimated gross development value of ₹3,800 crore.

news.title: EQT completes acquisition of Niwas Housing Finance
news.para: Niwas Housing Finance, formerly known as IndoStar Home Finance, is an affordable housing finance company with Rs 3000 crore ($ 359 million) in assets under management that has supported over 47,000 low income homeowners and small businesses across India

news.title: Consumer forum fines bank for losing customer’s property papers
news.para: The District Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission (DCDRC) has directed Noida Commercial Cooperative Bank to compensate a customer Rs 25,000 for losing his original property documents, along with Rs 5,000 for litigation costs. The bank admitted the documents were misplaced during a 2011 office relocation and was ordered to provide a certified duplicate and ensure the original deed is not misused.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 48 acres land parcel in Bengaluru
news.para: Godrej Properties has expanded its footprint in Bengaluru with the outright purchase of a 48-acre land parcel in Doddaballapur. This strategic acquisition will facilitate the development of plotted units, offering a development potential of 1.1 million sq ft.

news.title: One-stop property registry in the offing in Bhopal
news.para: Bhopal is streamlining property registration. A single-window system will soon combine sale deed and mortgage registration. This upgrade to the Sampada-2 software aims to launch before August 15. Buyers taking loans will only need one visit. The new system reduces paperwork and saves time for both citizens and staff. Property and mortgage papers will be registered together.

news.title: Goa's revenue department forms expert panel to study illegal homes built on private land
news.para: The Goa government has formed a 10-member expert committee. This committee will study the irregular use of land. It will also look into unauthorized construction on non-government land. The committee will recommend policies for sustainable land use. They will suggest measures for regularizing existing residential houses. The committee has three months to complete its study.

news.title: Form special team to probe property scam in Madurai: Madras HC
news.para: The Madras High Court has ordered a special investigation into a property tax scam within the Madurai Corporation. The court wants a senior IPS officer to lead the probe. This decision follows allegations of a significant revenue loss. T Ravi, an AIADMK councillor, raised concerns about the investigation's fairness.

news.title: Maharashtra government extends Nazul land amnesty scheme by a year
news.para: The Maharashtra government has extended its amnesty scheme for nazul land leases by another year, following a push by MLA Pravin Datke. The scheme, allowing conversion to Class-1 ownership at 2% of market rate, has seen overwhelming public response and increased revenue.

news.title: Indian Hotels net profit rises 26.56% to ₹329 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Indian Hotels Company Limited (IHCL) reported a 26.56% increase in net profit, reaching Rs 329.32 crore in Q1 FY26, driven by a 14% growth in hotel segment revenue. Despite geopolitical headwinds and recent incidents impacting topline by 2.5-3%, IHCL continues expansion with 12 new signings and 6 hotel openings.

news.title: IndiQube Spaces' ₹700-crore IPO to open on July 23
news.para: IndiQube Spaces has set the IPO price band at Rs 225-237 per share, aiming to raise Rs 700 crore. The IPO will be open from July 23-25, with a valuation of nearly Rs 5,000 crore at the upper end. The company intends to use the funds for expansion and debt repayment, with listing expected on July 30.

news.title: RERA has authority to take action against developers: Maharashtra minister
news.para: Maharashtra minister Uday Samant informed the assembly that RERA has the authority to act against developers for violations. This statement came in response to concerns raised about building permissions within Akot Municipal Council limits.

news.title: Rent compensation for residents to be cleared by month-end: Signature View Apartments RWA
news.para: The DDA has assured Signature View Apartments residents in Mukherjee Nagar that rent compensation will be cleared by the end of July, following the declaration of the 336-flat complex as structurally unsafe and slated for demolition.

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas posts ₹133.16 crore profit in Q1 FY26
news.para: Nuvoco Vistas Corp, the Nirma Group's building materials division, reported a significant profit increase to Rs 133.16 crore in Q1 FY26, driven by a 9% revenue increase to Rs 2,872.70 crore. The company achieved record first-quarter EBITDA through volume growth, premiumization, and strategic trade mix.

news.title: Sunteck Realty's profit rises 47% to ₹33.43 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Sunteck Realty Ltd witnessed a significant surge in net profit, reporting a 47% increase to Rs 33.43 crore in the first quarter of fiscal year 2025-26. While the real estate firm's total income experienced a decline, falling to Rs 201.53 crore, the company continues to be a leading developer with a strong presence in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region.

news.title: Smartworks Coworking Spaces shares jump over 9% in market debut trade
news.para: Smartworks Coworking Spaces Ltd shares closed with a 9% premium, ending at Rs 445.10 on the BSE and Rs 445.05 on the NSE. The IPO, priced at Rs 407, saw strong investor interest, being oversubscribed 13.45 times. The company intends to utilize the raised capital of Rs 583 crore for business expansion and debt reduction.
